The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Boycott threat

 Manchester: Manchester United fans say they could be leaving in droves following reports that Glazer plans to raise ticket prices by 54 per cent over the next five seasons. United fans groups said the prices will be out of their reach. 

People are so disillusioned with the massive increases they are being asked to pay, it will just turn more and more fans off, Nick Towle, chairman of Shareholders United, told BBC Radio five. 

 (AP) 




